{
  "texts": [
    "In deep learning object detection algorithms, the loss function typically combines the classification loss and localization loss, with their weights determining the ultimate optimization objective.Reference [66] proposed a strategy to deal with different-sized targets.",
    "In detecting medium-sized targets, they increased the network depth to extract more semantic features.",
    "When detecting small-sized targets, they introduced deconvolution and region mapping to obtain higher-resolution feature maps, which significantly improved the accuracy of detecting medium-sized and small-sized targets.Reference [67] introduced the Occlusion Loss to address the issue of occluded objects.",
    "By improving the match between predicted boxes and ground truth boxes, object localization became more accurate.",
    "Additionally, this approach mitigated the problem of one detection box corresponding to multiple objects, reducing instances of missed detections and significantly improving detection accuracy."
  ]
}